  "title": "Production Supervisor #79941",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Description</strong></p><ul><li>Industry/ Organization Type: Skin Care and Cosmetics Manufacturing</li><li>Position Title: <strong>Quality & Production Supervisor</strong></li><li>Working Location: North – Ang Mo Kio (Require taking few bus stops)</li><li>Working Hours: 5.5 days / Mon-Fri: 9am-6pm, Sat: 9am-1pm</li><li>Salary Package: <strong>Up to SGD 3000 + AWS + Variable Bonus</strong></li><li>Duration: Permanent</li><li></li></ul><p><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Lead, train, and coach team members to ensure effective performance and teamwork</li><li>Manage and oversee daily production activities, including purchasing, inventory control, stock management, and work scheduling</li><li>Participate actively in the entire production process from raw material preparation to the completion of finished products</li><li>Perform cleaning and basic troubleshooting of production machinery to ensure smooth operations</li><li>Oversee the full manufacturing process, including purchase requests, material withdrawal and issuance, and handover of finished goods to the warehouse</li><li>Create, maintain, and update records in the SAP system</li><li>Maintain and update ISO documentation, records, and related compliance materials</li><li>Support internal and external audit processes by ensuring proper documentation and adherence to standards</li><li>Coordinate with inter-departments to ensure production runs according to schedule</li><li>Perform any other tasks or assignments as directed by the Superior or Management</li><li></li><li></li></ul><p><strong>APPLY NOW!!!</strong></p><ul><li>Min. ITE in chemistry-related courses (Chemical Process Technology/Bio-Chemical Technology)</li><li>Min.3 years of working experience in related field</li><li>Experience in cosmetics, skincare, pharmaceutical, or chemical manufacturing is preferred</li><li>Knowledge of raw material testing, ingredient verification, and evaluation when there is a change of supplier</li><li>Basic understanding of quality control, ISO documentation, and audit requirements</li><li></li><li></li></ul><p>Kindly apply through <strong>ANY </strong>of the following methods:</p><ul><li>Submit your application by clicking the <strong>APPLY </strong>button;</li><li>Email your resume to <a href=\"mailto:Job@anradus.com.sg\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Job@anradus.com.sg</a>. Please indicate <strong>#79941 </strong>on the email subject.</li><li></li></ul><p><strong>Anradus Application Policy:</strong> We value each application and ensure every resume is reviewed. Our process is efficient, typically concluding within <strong>3 working days</strong>. If you do not receive communication from us within this timeframe, it's likely that your application has not been shortlisted by our client. In such cases, we recommend continuing your job search to maximize your opportunities.</p><p><br /><br /></p><p>Anradus Pte Ltd | EA License No. 20C0161 | Rachael Lee | EA Reg No.: R2093131</p>",
